      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum elastoplastic model with isotropic hardening for Ti-6Al-4V screw and rod; frictionless contact at screw-rod interface justified by lubricated test conditions. Model form uncertainty quantified via sensitivity analysis.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening (BISO) material model calibrated against coupon tensile data for Ti-6Al-4V ELI. Sensitivity analysis confirmed that ±10% variation in tangent modulus produces <3% change in yield force QoI. Model form uncertainty bounded and acceptable. Gradation 3 achieved."
