      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs assembled from production-representative lots. Six constructs tested at Lab A (FDA CDRH), five at Lab B (DePuy Synthes). Lot traceability documented. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions must cover at least two loading rates and two construct configurations to achieve Gradation 3; environmental conditioning (simulated body fluid) required for highest gradation.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted under a single quasi-static loading rate (5 mm/min) in ambient laboratory conditions only. No simulated physiological fluid environment was applied, and no secondary loading rate was evaluated. Only one construct configuration (standard 35 mm rod segment) was tested. These limitations restrict the achieved gradation to 2, one below the required level of 3. The team judged the single-condition dataset sufficient for the stated COU given that ASTM F1717 does not mandate multi-condition testing; however, this assessment does not fully satisfy the required credibility gradation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
