    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed their required gradation levels. The single shortfall in Test conditions (achieved Gradation 2 vs. required Gradation 3) was reviewed by the assessment team and judged not to materially affect the overall credibility conclusion given that ASTM F1717 is a standardized single-condition test and the quantitative output comparison metrics (E/uval < 1.96 for all QoIs) provide strong direct evidence of model accuracy. Overall assurance level is assessed as Medium, consistent with a Model Risk Level 3 device and the observed factor profile. Decision: Accepted.",
